1 sheet ([1] p.)
s.n., [London : 1660]
Verse - "More sacks to the mill, here comes a fresh wit,". Imprint from Wing. Annotation on Thomason copy: "Jan. 11. 1659". In two states: a) third line of title ends "handled,"; b) third line of title ends "Handled." Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
